messages.message: The duplication of the org / workspace name in this element looks strange. I think it would look better if the second line said ‘Overview’ and the same for the hyperlink in the second screenshot.
are these always the same? @Xindi Xu

We recently migrated all username and emails to use lowercase. There are a bunch UIs relying on the assumption that the personal workspace name = username. See https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C04TSMWLPAS/p1700100432259529.

Basically, if the personal workspace name = username, this won't happen and the user will see the attached screens


cc @Weiming Wu

let us know your thoughts on the attached screens! The overview doesn't use hyperlink because the overview page is the "my hub overview" page is the current page where the element sits, so there's nowhere to link :sweat_smile:
@Xindi Xu wonder if the easy fix here is that "My workspace overview" just becomes "Overview".
